                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting is characterized by upright to slightly left-sloping letters, uneven and not uniform (also number of the lines pro page is not constant), at times creating an impression of more than hands involved in writing. In fols. 61r, 71vb, 72va, the handwriting appears different: broader strokes, less carefully executed with a different tone of black ink.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Some distinct features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
-  መ (esp. in the 1st and 2nd orders) has loops of triangular shape, with the left loop more sharply pointed<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
- the upper horizontal strokes of some letters (e.g., መ ሠ በ) are uniformly slanted to the left<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
- some letters have rounded upper strokes, e.g., the letter ገ in the 6th order<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">
- the 6th order marker of ጰ  is set up on the  vertical stroke at the top and oriented to the left (e.g., fols. 11ra l.24, 45va l.19)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic">
- the 6th order marker of the letter የ has a very short and downwards oriented left part, and a long, upwards oriented right part (e.g., fols. 45vb l.5);  in the 4th order, the marker is diagonal and going down below the ruling (e.g., fol. 45vb l.7); the letters ኀ and ቀ in the 4th order show the same feature<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic">
- the loop marking the 7th order of letter ቀ is very pronounced, broad and elevates above other signs<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic">
- ፲ appears occasionally in the form with a ring attached to the right side through a horizontal stroke (fol. 135vb l.7).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
